{"name": "commentjson", "metadata": {"name": "commentjson", "version": "0.9.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python"], "home_page": "https://github.com/vaidik/commentjson", "license": "", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Add Python and JavaScript style comments in your JSON files.", "upload_time": 1601923746}, "documentation": ["# commentjson\n\n`commentjson` (Comment JSON) is a Python package that helps you create JSON\nfiles with Python and JavaScript style inline comments. Its API is very similar\nto the Python standard library's [json] module.\n\n```{image} https://travis-ci.org/vaidik/commentjson.png\n```\n\n## Installation\n\n> pip install commentjson\n\n## Basic Usage\n\n```python\n>>> import commentjson\n>>>\n>>> json_string = \"\"\"{\n...     \"name\": \"Vaidik Kapoor\", # Person's name\n...     \"location\": \"Delhi, India\", // Person's location\n...\n...     # Section contains info about\n...     // person's appearance\n...     \"appearance\": {\n...         \"hair_color\": \"black\",\n...         \"eyes_color\": \"black\",\n...         \"height\": \"6\"\n...     }\n... }\"\"\"\n>>>\n>>> json_loaded = commentjson.loads(json_string)\n>>> print json_loaded\n{u'appearance': {u'eyes_color': u'black', u'hair_color': u'black', u'height': u'6'}, u'name': u'Vaidik Kapoor', u'location': u'Delhi, India'}\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\nComplete documentation can be found [here].\n\n## Tests\n\n> python setup.py test\n\n## License\n\nSee [license].\n\n[here]: http://commentjson.readthedocs.org/en/latest/\n[json]: http://docs.python.org/2/library/json.html\n[license]: https://github.com/vaidik/commentjson/blob/master/LICENSE.rst\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.install_requires", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.description", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.pat