e` instance containing a JSON\ndocument with Python or JavaScript like comments) to a Python object.\n\n```\nparam text\n\nserialized JSON string with or without comments.\n\nparam kwargs\n\nall the arguments that json.loads accepts.\n\nreturns\n\ndict or list.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "commentjson.commentjson.dumps", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Serialize `obj` to a JSON formatted `str`. Accepts the same arguments\nas `json` module in stdlib.\n\n```\nparam obj\n\na JSON serializable Python object.\n\nparam kwargs\n\nall the arguments that json.dumps accepts.\n\nraises\n\ncommentjson.JSONLibraryException\n\nreturns str\n\nserialized string.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "commentjson.commentjson.load", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Deserialize `fp` (a `.read()`-supporting file-like object containing a\nJSON document with Python or JavaScript like comments) to a Python object.\n\n```\nparam fp\n\na -supporting file-like object containing a JSON\ndocument with or without comments.\n\nparam kwargs\n\nall the arguments that json.load accepts.\n\nraises\n\ncommentjson.JSONLibraryException\n\nreturns\n\ndict or list.\n```\n"]}, {"name": "commentjson.commentjson.dump", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fp", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Serialize `obj` as a JSON formatted stream to `fp` (a\n`.write()`-supporting file-like object). Accepts the same arguments as\n`json` module in stdlib.\n\n```\nparam obj\n\na JSON serializable Python object.\n\nparam fp\n\na -supporting file-like object containing a JSON\ndocument with or without comments.\n\nparam kwargs\n\nall the arguments that json.dump accepts.\n\nraises\n\ncommentjson.JSONLibraryException\n```\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "commentjson.commentjson.parser", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "commentjson.commentjson.serializer", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "commentjson.commentjson.BaseException", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [{"name": "commentjson.commentjson.BaseException.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exc", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base exception to be implemented and raised while handling exceptions\nraised by libraries used in `commentjson`.\n\nSets message of self in a way that it clearly calls out that the exception\nwas raised by another library, along with the entire stacktrace of the\nexception raised by the other library."]}, {"name": "commentjson.commentjson.ParserException", "bases": ["BaseException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "commentjson.commentjson.ParserException.library", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception raised when the `lark` raises an exception i.e.\nthe exception is not caused by `commentjson` and caused by the use of\n`lark` in `commentjson`."]}, {"name": "commentjson.commentjson.JSONLibraryException", "bases": ["BaseException"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "commentjson.commentjson.JSONLibraryException.library", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception raised when the `json` raises an exception i.e.\nthe exception is not caused by `commentjson` and caused by the use of\n`json` in `commentjson`.\n\n:::{note}\nAs of now, `commentjson` supports only standard library's `json`\nmodule. It might start supporting other widely-used contributed JSON\nlibraries in the future.\n:::\n"]}], "exports": []}]}